## Project Structure

This project follows **feature-first architecture** from [project-readability](../project-readability/):

\`\`\`
{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout
│   ├── page.tsx          # Home page
│   └── (auth)/           # Auth route group
├── features/             # Feature modules
│   ├── auth/             # Authentication feature
│   └── home/             # Home feature
├── shared/               # Shared code
│   ├── components/       # Reusable components
│   ├── lib/              # Utilities
│   └── types/            # TypeScript types
└── public/               # Static assets
\`\`\`

### Key Principles

- **Feature-first:** Code organized by feature, not by type
- **Colocation:** Related code stays together
- **Boring over clever:** Familiar patterns, easy to understand
- **Flat structure:** Maximum 3 levels deep

## Available Scripts

- \`npm run dev\` - Start development server
- \`npm run build\` - Build for production
- \`npm run start\` - Start production server
- \`npm run lint\` - Run ESLint
- \`npm run type-check\` - Check TypeScript types
{{#if hasDatabase}}- \`npm run prisma:generate\` - Generate Prisma client
- \`npm run prisma:push\` - Push schema to database
- \`npm run prisma:studio\` - Open Prisma Studio{{/if}}

